 <text id="A2526T">
  <front id="d2">
   <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
    <p>A brief not from Hotchkiss to his wife, telling of recent bad weather and its effects on the
     soldiers.</p>
   </div1>
  </front>

  <body id="d4">
   <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
    <head>
     <name type="recipient">Sara A. Hotchkiss</name>
    </head>

    <opener>
     <dateline>
      <date value="1862-04-10">Thursday April 10<hi rend="super">th</hi> 1862</date>
      <name type="place">Mr. Rude's</name>
     </dateline>
     <salute>My <abbr expan="Dear">Dr</abbr> Wife:</salute>
    </opener>

    <p> We have had 3 days of uninterrupted storm, terrible to soldiers, and our men have <orig
      reg="suffered">sufferd</orig> much, though they have been in their tents &amp; have kept
     up fires as best they could, I am still fortunately under a hospitable roof, and by a good fire
     for which I am certainly thankful -- we are still in the same situation -- no news. I hope Anna
     is doing well -- I am anxious to hear from you, but suppose the mail is interrupted -- the mail
     is now going -- so good bye &amp; god bless you -- I am perfectly well -- </p>

    <closer>
     <salute>Your <abbr expan="affectionate">aff.</abbr> husband</salute>
     <signed>Jed. Hotchkiss</signed>
    </closer>
   </div1>
  </body>
 </text>
